<subSubSection id="D52CBB1489740744F7FE6F97B5AC5689" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="572715682BA52D42173D17FC025577A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2364A9F14FC5FAECFFEA753A025E3D33" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DC268F2F3777EF42C5B40B7CC3F10643" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quadrula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrula">
<emphasis id="41803B0FE00419E530BDD49CD1D5AB22" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. quadrula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hardy from Thailand, Cambodia and Vietnam in the presence of two broad quadrate areas in wing cell r1, an enlarged basal discal spot in cell r4+5 and large, broad hyaline indentations in cell cua. It can be differentiated by the lack of silvery facial spots and white rather than silvery parafacial stripes in males, as well as the angulate posterior wing margin, pterostigma predominantly fulvous/yellow and pale brown, and epandrium of uniform width throughout its length, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="681192FDD534FB035F0C078E5BB0FB20" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quadrula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrula">
<emphasis id="13FD1733E0233033947BA5EA2C96315A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. quadrula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the parafacial is silvery rather than white and facial silvery spots are present lateroventrally in males, the wing is evenly rounded posteriorly, the pterostigma is hyaline basally and dark brown apically, and the epandrium tapers apically. This species was mistakenly listed as 
<taxonomicName id="87E59BFBBA0E6D2C0DD34B6631945A7F" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quadrula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrula">
<emphasis id="0709179F15E22EA2A84ABF31A609E5DC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. quadrula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from India by 
<bibRefCitation id="EAF536A6534AFFAD36C95AF49573025C" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7A4C32DF5322E041E68EF774EE7D4ABE" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph id="E8E8D1FD3079C15DD6EB9E5AB06B5BDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D9A90064A1EF67347133DC9D3FFD5D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="90FE13797AE54FEC527DE6BD79CBA21E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Male.</emphasis>
Medium-sized fly (4.10-4.99 mm long) with broad, angulate wing with fulvous markings (Figs 
<figureCitation id="358FAE3E06458716A50947B9081A88CB" captionStart="Figures 9–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 10. Habitus of Platensina flavistigma David &amp; Hancock, sp. nov. 9 dorsal view 10 lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669199" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="10991BEEA855684B4B1BF502A3AC3EC9" captionStart="Figures 9–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 10. Habitus of Platensina flavistigma David &amp; Hancock, sp. nov. 9 dorsal view 10 lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669199" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="C4F5FB868A773B43002200A8B615D04F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669199" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figures 9–10" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="A014D75E1A5D6CEF32805460EE1FC801" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="2C7E462B19FD8E4295DEFF8BEE862EB5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Figures 9-10.</emphasis>
Habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4A0C2797F012ACAFA0EB01939E00D8F5" authorityName="David &amp; Hancock" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina flavistigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavistigma">
<emphasis id="1E8D7CED73B85BE802F4327AD3BF1E53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Platensina flavistigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
David &amp; Hancock, sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="19055F10194A38FA5338E9B615D12087" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">9</emphasis>
dorsal view 
<emphasis id="A6C4DB866FB0DAD2F177947589CD10F7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">10</emphasis>
lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="0FE1B193E40F9581D7F21A1393E08117" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="4FC1584D7391806CE9459D6F2AE0EA7C" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Head</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="3D3009F0402D42371CD0D0361FFAA43A" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. Platensina flavistigma David &amp; Hancock, sp. nov. 11 head (profile view) 12 head (frontal view) 13 abdomen (dorsal view) 14 thorax (lateral view) and legs 15 scutum 16 wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669200" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="005DB41E984B8D78B932F01DF4CB3866" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. Platensina flavistigma David &amp; Hancock, sp. nov. 11 head (profile view) 12 head (frontal view) 13 abdomen (dorsal view) 14 thorax (lateral view) and legs 15 scutum 16 wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669200" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">12</figureCitation>
). as high as long; frons fulvous with three pairs of frontal setae and two pairs of orbital setae; ocellar triangle dark brown, with well-developed ocellar seta; medial vertical seta black; lateral vertical seta, paravertical seta and postocellar setae white; postocular setae black interspersed with prominent, white lanceolate setae. Face fulvous with broad orange-brown patches on ventral half of antennal groove. Scape and pedicel fulvous, first flagellomere shorter than face, concolorous with frons, arista short pilose. Parafacial alongside ventral half of face distinctly whitish. Gena narrow, with prominent genal seta, subvibrissal setae present.
</paragraph>
<caption id="23C5EF5DC17022A48BE9E2B770807D56" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669200" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figures 11–16" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="1297F8DA17B7E064A4F1F6AE857FAF49" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="3A5C70B7B47B186EFC3227621E62D4F5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Figures 11-16.</emphasis>
