</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8F559857DE90D43E4C60686CBAB1DE7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E664C9FFF838C93402AFC5457FE2B9F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E2618D486FAEFA7C76049082DF3F478" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The specific name is derived from two Latin words 
<emphasis id="FBEFA89AF61F81E86435E77C226EDC00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">flavus</emphasis>
(=yellow) and 
<emphasis id="1854D98573A38594C000157D48036AE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">stigma</emphasis>
(=ptersotigma).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
